{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2",
    "translationId": "eob",
    "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Corinthians 2 in Eastern Greek Orthodox Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.1",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:1",
      "text": "But I resolved this for myself: that I would not return to you in sorrow.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.2",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:2",
      "text": "If whom I grieve?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.3",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:3",
      "text": "Indeed, I wrote as I did, so that when I came, I would not have sorrow from the ones who should be me joy; but I trust in you all, that my joy would also be shared by all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.4",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:4",
      "text": "It was out of much affliction and anguish of heart that I wrote to you with many tears, not to cause you distress but to let you know what overflowing love I have for you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.5",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:5",
      "text": "Still, if anyone has caused sorrow, he has caused sorrow not to only me but also, to an extent, to all of you.b",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.6",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:6",
      "text": "For this person, the punishment imposed by the many [of you] should be enough.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.7",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:7",
      "text": "In fact, you should rather forgive and comfort this person, for fear that he might be overwhelmed with excessive sorrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.8",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:8",
      "text": "Therefore, I beg you to confirm your love toward him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.9",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:9",
      "text": "I had also written with this purpose: that I might know by a test whether you are obedient in all things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.10",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:10",
      "text": "Now, I also forgive whoever you forgive! Indeed, if Christ, 11so that Satan may not gain any ground over us; and we are not ignorant of his schemes. Paul’s ministry",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.12",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:12",
      "text": "Now, when I came to Troas for the Good News of Christ as a door was opened to me in the Lord,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.13",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:13",
      "text": "I had no relief for my spirit, because I did not find Titus, my brother. After taking my leave of them [in Troas], I headed into Macedonia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.14",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:14",
      "text": "Thanks be to God, who always leads us in triumph in",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.15",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:15",
      "text": "Indeed, we are a sweet fragrance of Christ to God, both in those who are being saved and in those who are perishing.a",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.16",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:16",
      "text": "To the latter, we are a stench from death to death, but to the first [we are] a sweet fragrance from life to life. Who is equal to such a task?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.17",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:17",
      "text": "We are not as many who ‘peddle the word of God,’ but we speak in Christ with sincerity, as from God and in the sight of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "eob:second-corinthians.2.402",
      "translationId": "eob",
      "bookSlug": "second-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 402,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Corinthians 2:402",
      "text": "every place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
